Since I moved to the Bronx I did alot of pizza hunting since pizza is my favorite comport food,and honesty dinner too. I visited 4 pizza stores in my area and starting with the least expensive one which is Villa pizza; I can honestly say its among the worst pizza I ever ate. Then theres Rocco's pizza, I would recomend it to anybody who doesn't know what really good pizza taste like,plus its only $17 for large sausage pie,which is dollar cheaper than Jeromes.finially across the street from Rocco's is bedfords pizza. Lets just say not only would i never go back there , i cross the street when i get there. So the choice is yours, pay more but you will get the best tasting pizza at jeromes. Oh and there are two types of large pizza, the large that easily fits into the box, and the large pizza that cant fit into the box without the crust folding over cause its too big. Now thats a LARGE pizza,and for the record 3 of the 4 stores use the identical same box: delicious pizza on side & 0pizzeria0 on top. So its not the box size. Jerome's makes a much larger large pizza to go with a much better quality- tasting pizza.
